\section*{Solving a Quadratic Equation} %* removes numbering for section
The quadratic formula is given by:
\begin{equation}
 x = \frac{-b \pm \sqrt{b^2 - 4ac}}{2a}
\end{equation}
ubstituting the values a = 1, b = 2, and c = -8 into the formula:
\begin{equation}
 x = \frac{-2 \pm \sqrt{2^2 - 4(1)(-8)}}{2 \cdot 1}
\end{equation}
Simplifying further:
\begin{equation}
 x = \frac{-2 \pm \sqrt{4 + 32}}{2}
\end{equation}
To get final answer:
\begin{equation}
x= -1 \pm 3
\end{equation}
